<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-21T05:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-21T05:30:00-05:00" n="379" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">856D.13/5–2151: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Indonesia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cochran</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Djakarta</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-21T18:00:00+07:30">May
                                        21, 1951—6 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1624. Djuanda told me 21st that mtg Econ Fin Comite 17th question
                                gold sales not discussed. He said responsible authorities <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Govt now so generally opposed to
                                this idea that he convinced it will be abandoned without necessity
                                Cabinet decision (see <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                                    1603).<note n="1" xml:id="d379fn1">Not printed; see the first
                                    footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_647">p. 647</ref>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cochran</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>